    "innerHtml": "'Miss Hale, I was very ungrateful yesterday—'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'You had nothing to be grateful for,' said she, raising her eyes, and\nlooking full and straight at him. 'You mean, I suppose, that you believe\nyou ought to thank me for what I did.' In spite of herself—in defiance\nof her anger—the thick blushes came all over her face, and burnt into\nher very eyes; which fell not nevertheless from their grave and steady\nlook. 'It was only a natural instinct; any woman would have done just\nthe same. We all feel the sanctity of our sex as a high privilege when\nwe see danger. I ought rather,' said she, hastily, 'to apologise to you,\nfor having said thoughtless words which sent you down into the danger.'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
