  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'We must send Martha away in good time. It would never do to have her\nhere when he comes, and then send her off in a hurry.'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'Dixon is sure to remind us of that. I was thinking that, if we wanted\nany help in the house while he is here, we could perhaps get Mary\nHiggins. She is very slack of work, and is a good girl, and would take\npains to do her best, I am sure, and would sleep at home, and need never\ncome upstairs, so as to know who is in the house.'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'As you please. As Dixon pleases. But, Margaret, don't get to use these\nhorrid Milton words. \"Slack of work:\" it is a provincialism. What will\nyour aunt Shaw say, if she hears you use it on her return?'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'Oh, mamma! don't try and make a bugbear of aunt Shaw' said Margaret,\nlaughing. 'Edith picked up all sorts of military slang from Captain\nLennox, and aunt Shaw never took any notice of it.'"
